cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and language grounding. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end trainable neural architecture for task-oriented language grounding. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is relevant as the proposed model uses reinforcement and imitation learning methods. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the model takes raw pixels from the environment as input and maps it to visual elements. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also relevant as the paper deals with mapping language instructions to actions in the environment, which is a common problem in robotics.
